Looking ahead into 2023 and taking inventory on the rewarding areas in my life I’d like to commit more time to as well as my schedule,I wanted to jump on here to say that I currently have the space to broaden my music instructor/accountability partner availability. 
I’ve got this online meeting thing pretty ironed out and my methods show appropriately solid results in my students when applied. Ultimately, If I’m not able to help you with what you want to know, I’m pretty confident I can connect you with someone who can. 
Currently and always seeking seekers of all shapes, sizes, ages, abilities and time zones! Anyone looking to develop specific skills, fill in gaps, correct some bad habits or just have passionate discussions about musicianship. 
I don’t subscribe to a one sized fits all method, each person has unique goals, aspirations, and learning styles which require a unique approach. My focus is always on making learning fun and efficient. 
That said, we’ll most likely explore the fundamentals of theory ie harmony, rhythm, arrangement and composition, building chords and related scales, transcribing by ear, reading chord charts, improvisation along with various playing techniques mixed with real world examples and stories. 
If this message reverberates with you in any way, reach out or click on the links in the usual places to schedule something.

The homies at @totaldissonanceworship have let this feral cat out of the bag, pre-orders are up through their page…I’m copy-pasta’ing their post because I can’t re-word it any better than they already have…

PALLID VEIL - Pallid Veil 7" (single-sided)

Today, we are honored to present the Pallid Veil 7" in two splatter colors and an ultra rare hand-pour variant via totaldissonanceworship.com.

Pallid Veil is a project with a line-up that is nothing short of an all star cast of forward-thinking, extreme music veterans:

Luc Lemay (Gorguts) - Guitar, Vocals
Dave Davidson (Revocation, Gargoyl) - Guitar
Liam Wilson (The Dillinger Escape Plan, John Frum, Azusa) - Bass
Elliot Hoffman (Car Bomb) - Drums

Formerly only available on YouTube as part of Metal Injection’s Slay at Home streaming event, we were finally able to give the self-titled song the release it always deserved!

If you like your Death Metal discordant, truly heavy and deeply profound, this special release is one not to miss.

#pallidveil #gorguts #revocation #thedillingerescapeplan #johnfrum #azusaband #carbomb
Amped to jump back in the saddle with @InFlames this summer. Absolute whirlwind but it all fell into place last night - thank you @release_athens 🔥

@graspopmetalmeeting was next level! The crowd was like a mass electrocution, such sick energy! Did my best to keep that feedback loop of intensity flowing! @lisebergab and @tonsofrock up next, but first, @metallica in Gothenburg tonight! Missing my family on this Father’s Day, but can’t deny how warm the “feels like family” vibes are with the whole @inflames camp, I’m honored to spend it with them instead! #gmm23 #inflames
Before & After. Tack! Tack! Tack! #inflames

In the presence of greatness! Had an incredible time hanging out with the genius himself, @dougdarkglass, meeting his friendly staff, test driving his envy-inducing treasure trove of basses and getting a sneak peek under the hood at the @darkglassofficial and @neuraldsp offices in Helsinki. 🤤🔂
Looking forward ending this crazy year playing with In Flames and supporting Meshuggah on a lap around North America with White Chapel (and Voivod!).

Fastening my seatbelt and putting my tray in the upright position for this next run of Euro fests with @inflames. First up -  @metaldays.festival.official and @rockstadtextremefest.official.
I’ve never played Romania 🇷🇴before, that’s gonna be pretty rad!

📸 @brandlicht from @rockharzopenair

I think that was my 5th time playing @brutal.assault?!? Always one of my favorites, the lineups, the setting, and I’ve come to expect running into a few good people I absolutely didn’t expect to see there, and this one was no different. I know I missed just as many friends too. Looking forward to the next time, and more importantly towards @reloadfestivalofficial , @summerbreezeopenair and @dynamometalfest this weekend!
📸 @libi_photo

I’ve been sleeping around a bit with this Keisel A2. I needed something versatile for when I’m doing my homework in the woodshed between fests. I’ve had my eyes on one of these more modern designs for a minute now and all the build options @kieselguitars offered spoke to me at the right time…Walnut neck? Yes please. Fanned frets? If not now, when? 

The @darkglasselectronics preamp paired with the proprietary pickups are super punchy and sensitive! I had the bass sitting right against my stomach as it gurgled (that’s called ‘borborygmy’ btw - look it up!) and I could hear it in my headphones through the pickups! Wild! 

Really enjoying reaching for this as my EDC bass. Thanks @c333j_ and #kieselguitars!
I'm not even the second most talented. But at least my lack of skills is consistent.

And…that’s a wrap! Summer 2023, you were a real blindside! I’m beyond grateful to all the people behind the scenes making all these festivals happen - the event staff, catering, promoters, agents, drivers, all the crews - especially ours, the way you bleed for me/us doesn’t go unnoticed. To all the incredible musicians we crossed paths with, namely @fitforanautopsy and @killswitchengage - looking forward to smashing stages with y’all again! To my bandmates - @andersfridn @bgelotte @chris_broderick_guitar @tannerwayne @nielsnielsen - thanks for your trust, inspiration and for treating me like a brother from day one, you all had me at “Hello.” Of course it wouldn’t be worth it without all you feral fans who rocked out to @inflames this summer, especially to those who came and closed it out with us at this years Dalhalla Brinner. The weather was harsh, but the atmosphere was fantastic and the elements didn’t seem to phase you. It was a real honor to perform for you in that very special place. Overall, thanks to all of you for the warm welcome into this Jesterhead race.
#InFlamesWeTrust 📸 @bilivegas
Impromptu photo shoot backstage at Brutal Assault, Josefov Fortress, Czech Republic. 📸 @mmarrikk

A couple shots from Summer Breeze Open Air. 
📸 @dany.adelfinger

Cntl+Alt+Del but for my neck.
 📸: @bilivegas
It’s my favorite adult person and my partner in parenting crimes @jessicacurreri’s solar return, and I’m wishing her the best day and happiest new year ever. I couldn’t be me without you, babe. 😍😘
Contrast aids focus. 📸 @sharbel.kanoun from @hellfestopenair

Just added a few more @inflames dates with my dude @nickshinz and @havokband - there’s for sure gonna be some nerdy bassin’ going down backstage on this little pre-party before our adventure with @meshuggah and @whitechapelband. Looking forward to stomping stages again! But first, Mexico, South and Central America! Roll call! 📢
End of Summer. Abstract Moments.

Tracing the contours of my Johari Window.
📸 @bilivegas

Hitting the road again so soon, starting with @hhopenair in Mexico, then continuing on to Ecuador, Chile, Argentina, Brazil, Colombia, Costa Rica…and then straight into US/Canada with @meshuggah / @whitechapelband to close the year. Stoked!  Killer shots by @stephaniedcabral from @hellfestopenair
Hybrid Moments

South America, you’re a hot mess I just can’t quit, I love the authentic rawness of everything, and I’ll never forget all the “Olé!” Chants! The street art was insane, especially in Bogota - next level! Is it true Justin Bieber kicked off a revolution with a tribute to his dead hamster? Darshan with the Andes is something profound. Can’t quite articulate just how perfect of a place Costa Rica is. Looking forward to reconnecting with people and places in America and Canada I haven’t seen in some time.
Just announced, we’ll be shredding through Europe next Fall with @archenemyofficial & @soilwork!
Calgary Tonight, LFG! 📸 @limsangphotography
Winnipeg tonight, then back to the states for Minneapolis tomorrow and Madison Saturday - all sold out! 📸 @limsangphotography

Getting dialed into these new digs a little more every night. 
Rad shot from Edmonton via @mikey.photograph

Killer show at the Paramount in Huntington, NY last night - every band is dialed up and that raw East Coast energy was in full effect. Ripping through Boston tonight @ MGM Music Hall. 📸 @kevinwilsonnyc
Go for launch, L-minus 192 days.
Two-Stage-To-Orbit
Orbiter reentry and landing sequence.

Coming down to the wire…Bethlehem tonight: As close to a homecoming show as I’m gonna get! A few tickets left, and let me tell ya, if you don’t buy them, then the Cowboys automatically go to the Super Bowl, and no one wants that on their conscience. 🦅 📸 @nathanielshannon

Fall Tour complete, holiday R&R engaged. 🎄
Some random takeaways and highlights:

— I woke up to new mountain ranges almost daily, from the Cerro El Plomo to Mt Forbes
- playing Navajo Nation / Window Rock, AZ - truly an honor 
- Getting reacquainted with my 2D days with @bgelotte as my accountability partner
- Reconnecting with all the friends and family I haven’t seen since the last time I was doing laps around the globe with any sort of frequency. 
- Meeting flocks of diehard In Flames fans every night; it’s an honor and blessing I don’t take for granted to meet your standards and be welcomed in such an open way. #IFWT
- Feeling beyond grateful to still create such special connections deep into adulthood with my new @inflames family. It’s a genuinely unique vibe that sets my heart ablaze. To @andersfridn , @bgelotte @tannerwayne @chris_broderick_guitar (and of course @nielsnielsen !) thanks for your trust and support, and to and the rest of the best, ie. our crew, thanks for the laughter through the tears and all the magic spells you’re constantly casting to keep this show on the road. We truly couldn’t do it without you. 
- To @havokband @whitechapelband @meshuggah @voivodofficial and all the other bands we crossed paths with in support of the riffs, the passion you all put into your craft is inspirational.
44 is a feeling.

Bassist: @inflames/@dillingerescapeplan/ @azusaofficial/@John_Frum/.
